AS INTRODUCED
6
7
An Act relating to municipalities; subjecting
7
campsites on municipal land to certain review by the
8
Department of Environmental Quality and the
8
Department of Public Safety; providing for the
9
promulgation of rules; providing for codification;
9
and providing an effective date.
10
10
11
11
12
BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
12
13
SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
13
14
in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 43-117 of Title 11, unless there
14
15
is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
15
16
A. Any campsite on land within a municipality shall be subject
16
17
to evaluation by the Department of Environmental Quality and the
17
18
Department of Public Safety if such campsite has been utilized by
18
19
ten or more individuals for more than five (5) days. Such
19
20
evaluation shall be based on basic environmental and sanitation
20
21
standards.
21
22
B. The Department of Environmental Quality and the Department
22
23
of Public Safety shall promulgate rules to effectuate the provisions
23
24
of this section.
24
Req. No. 2196 Page 1

1
SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
